{"award_age":67.0,"bio_image":"full\/3d8e99895cb46cdb5b6c7fb232d7b530a171d53a.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"Canada","date_of_birth":"1932-10-24T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/8\/89\/Rmundell.jpg\/180px-Rmundell.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_Mundell","mini_bio":"<p><b>Robert Alexander Mundell<\/b>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_Canada\" title=\"Order of Canada\">CC<\/a> (born October 24, 1932) is a Nobel Prize-winning Canadian <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economist\" title=\"Economist\">economist<\/a>. Mundell is a professor of economics at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chinese_University_of_Hong_Kong\" title=\"Chinese University of Hong Kong\">Chinese University of Hong Kong<\/a>.<\/p><p>He received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economics\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economics<\/a> in 1999 for his pioneering work in monetary dynamics and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Optimum_currency_area\" title=\"Optimum currency area\">optimum currency areas<\/a>. Mundell is known as the \"father\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_Mundell#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Euro\" title=\"Euro\">euro<\/a>, as he laid the groundwork for its introduction through this work and helped to start the movement known as <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Supply-side_economics\" title=\"Supply-side economics\">supply-side economics<\/a>. Mundell is also known for the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mundell%E2%80%93Fleming_model\" title=\"Mundell\u2013Fleming model\">Mundell\u2013Fleming model<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mundell%E2%80%93Tobin_effect\" title=\"Mundell\u2013Tobin effect\">Mundell\u2013Tobin effect<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Robert Mundell","place_of_birth":"Kingston, Ontario ,  Canada","place_of_death":null,"text":"Robert Mundell , Economics, 1999","year":1999.0}